pacman.model

Class Maze

  • java.lang.Object
    • pacman.model.Maze

  • public class Maze
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is an ADT that represents a pacman map. The data is represented by a 2-dimensional array. Data located at data[y][x] contains the detail of the cell: (x,y) represents the position on the map with x horizontal y vertical and the origin (0,0) in the upper left corner.
    Version:
    1.0

      • data

        private final int[][] data
        Contains the detail of the grid. Data is accessed via grid[y][x] where (x,y) are positions on a Pacman map with x horizontal, y vertical and the origin (0,0) in the upper left corner.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Maze

        public Maze(int width,
            int height,
            int[][] data,
            java.util.Set<Coordinate> pacmanStartLocations,
            java.util.Set<Coordinate> ghostStartLocations)
        This is the constructor of the grid, which creates a board with specified initial values.
        Parameters:
        width - the width of the grid
        height - the height of the grid
        data - the pre-configured grid detail
        pacmanStartLocations - the pre-configured starter positions for pacman
        ghostStartLocations - the pre-configured starter positions for ghosts
        Requires:
        width >= 0 & height >= 0 & data.length == height & for row in data row.length == width
        Modifies:
        width, height, data, pacmanStartLocations, ghostStartLocations
        Effects:
        this.width = width, this.height = height this.data = data this.pacman = pacman this.ghosts = ghosts
